(2) Probably it was this law that gave the final extension to the principle of Cato by granting im- munity from the degrading punishments in question to citizens” serving in the Roman armies, It did not lessen’ the plenary imperium of the general; against this there was still to be no appeal. Nor did it abolish the punishment of death; it forbade the scourging of citizens with the cat (verbera)¹’, and henceforth even the execution of a citizen by order of a court martial had to be carried out in a less⁸⁰ degrading manner.
